data.description: This rare infill parcel located just 4 Blocks south of Prescott's Downtown is one of few vacant land opportunities in the downtown area. Bordering Aspen Creek near the confluence of Granite Creek the gently sloping terrain is enhanced by pines, meadows and boulder outcroppings. With strong barriers to entry in downtown Prescott this secluded parcel is poised for development with easy access to everything downtown and the recreation opportunities in the national forest to the south and west.BG zoning allows many uses in commercial and residential categories. Buyer to verify use with the City. The +/-2.35 acres to be split in escrow, reserving +/-1 acre for Sellers personal residence. Access  willl be at South end of S McCormick through a yet to be constructed road across Aspen Creek.
